Nicolas Bourbaki is the pseudonym of a group of (mainly) French mathematicians who publish an authoritative account of contemporary mathematics.


More information is available in two articles:


Bourbaki: the pre-war years and Bourbaki: the post-war years


The founding members of the organisation were:


Henri Cartan

Claude Chevalley

Jean Coulomb

Jean Delsarte

Jean Dieudonné

Charles Ehresmann

Szolem Mandelbrojt

René de Possel

André Weil